CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1962, pg. 1, reads: "All-Day 'Rights' Probe Reveals Pittsburgh Suffering from Bias - Attentive audience greeted speakers at the CIC [Catholic Interracial Council] Civil Rights Rally."
TitMainTitle: Audience of women and men, seated in ballroom of Penn Sheraton Hotel for the Catholic Interracial Council of Pittsburgh civil rights rally
